<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I am experimenting with Emacs and trying to make some weird key-bindings just as a playful activity. I know that something simple like this works fine:</p> <pre><code>(global-unset-key (kbd &quot;/&quot;)) (global-set-key (kbd &quot;/ s&quot;) &#39;save-buffer) </code></pre> <p>Now I can type <code>/s</code> to save the current buffer and I can type <code>C-q /</code> when I need to insert a literal <code>/</code>.</p> <p>But can I now make a key binding where <code>/</code> is a modifier key? For example, can I somehow get this to work?</p> <pre><code>(global-unset-key (kbd &quot;/&quot;)) (global-set-key (kbd &quot;/-s&quot;) &#39;save-buffer) </code></pre> <p>This does not work for me of course. When I type <code>/-s</code> (press and hold <code>/</code>, press <code>s</code>, release <code>/</code>) I get this error,</p> <pre><code>/ s is undefined </code></pre> <p>I see why this error happens. But is there anyway to make this work and treat <code>/</code> as a modifier key?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/biggrben"> /u/biggrben </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/vx7qjs/can_i_use_a_nonmodifier_key_as_a_modifier_key_in/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/vx7qjs/can_i_use_a_nonmodifier_key_as_a_modifier_key_in/">[comments]</a></span>